<li id="cite_note-paint-15">^ <a href="#cite_ref-paint_15-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-paint_15-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-paint_15-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-paint_15-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/earth/main.jhtml?view=DETAILS&amp;grid=&amp;xml=/earth/2008/04/22/sciart122.xml" class="external text" title="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/earth/main.jhtml?view=DETAILS&amp;grid=&amp;xml=/earth/2008/04/22/sciart122.xml" rel="nofollow">"Oil painting 'invented in Asia, not Europe'"</a>. Telegraph.co.uk<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/earth/main.jhtml?view=DETAILS&amp;grid=&amp;xml=/earth/2008/04/22/sciart122.xml" class="external free" title="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/earth/main.jhtml?view=DETAILS&amp;grid=&amp;xml=/earth/2008/04/22/sciart122.xml" rel="nofollow">http://www.telegraph.co.uk/earth/main.jhtml?view=DETAILS&amp;grid=&amp;xml=/earth/2008/04/22/sciart122.xml</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 24 April 2008</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Oil+painting+%27invented+in+Asia%2C+not+Europe%27&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=Telegraph.co.uk&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraph.co.uk%2Fearth%2Fmain.jhtml%3Fview%3DDETAILS%26grid%3D%26xml%3D%2Fearth%2F2008%2F04%2F22%2Fsciart122.xml&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Buddhas_of_Bamyan"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> However, the press release picked up by media, clearly misdates the earliest uses of oil paint in Europe, which is well known to be fully described in a treatise by <a href="/wiki/Theophilus_Presbyter" title="Theophilus Presbyter">Theophilus Presbyter</a> of 1100-1120, and may date back to the Ancient Romans. See: Rutherford John Gettens, George Leslie Stout, 1966, Courier Dover Publications, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0486215970" class="internal">ISBN 0486215970</a> <a href="http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=bdQVgKWl3f4C&amp;pg=PA42&amp;dq=oil+painting+Theophilus&amp;sig=oEkZ_FzY5mTDvyXr-FE9GLyZu-o" class="external text" title="http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=bdQVgKWl3f4C&amp;pg=PA42&amp;dq=oil+painting+Theophilus&amp;sig=oEkZ_FzY5mTDvyXr-FE9GLyZu-o" rel="nofollow">Painting Materials: A Short Encyclopedia (online text)</a>, p.42<a href="http://www.hs-augsburg.de/~harsch/Chronologia/Lspost12/Theophilus/the_da00.html" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.hs-augsburg.de/~harsch/Chronologia/Lspost12/Theophilus/the_da00.html" rel="nofollow">[1]</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2008/04/080422083309.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2008/04/080422083309.htm" rel="nofollow">"Ancient Buddhist Paintings From Bamyan Were Made Of Oil, Hundreds Of Years Before Technique Was 'Invented' In Europe"</a>. Sciencedaily.com<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2008/04/080422083309.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2008/04/080422083309.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2008/04/080422083309.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 24 April 2008</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Ancient+Buddhist+Paintings+From+Bamyan+Were+Made+Of+Oil%2C+Hundreds+Of+Years+Before+Technique+Was+%27Invented%27+In+Europe&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=Sciencedaily.com&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedaily.com%2Freleases%2F2008%2F04%2F080422083309.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Buddhas_of_Bamyan"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-nature-17">^ <a href="#cite_ref-nature_17-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-nature_17-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-nature_17-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-nature_17-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-nature_17-4" title=""><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.nature.com/news/2008/080422/full/news.2008.770.html" class="external text" title="http://www.nature.com/news/2008/080422/full/news.2008.770.html" rel="nofollow">"Ancient Buddhas painted in oils"</a>. nature.com<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.nature.com/news/2008/080422/full/news.2008.770.html" class="external free" title="http://www.nature.com/news/2008/080422/full/news.2008.770.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.nature.com/news/2008/080422/full/news.2008.770.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 24 April 2008</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Ancient+Buddhas+painted+in+oils&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=nature.com&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Fnews%2F2008%2F080422%2Ffull%2Fnews.2008.770.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Buddhas_of_Bamyan"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.rferl.org/Content/Archeologists_Find_Giant_Sleeping_Buddha_In_Afghanistan_/1197572.html" class="external text" title="http://www.rferl.org/Content/Archeologists_Find_Giant_Sleeping_Buddha_In_Afghanistan_/1197572.html" rel="nofollow">"Archaeologists Find Giant 'Sleeping' Buddha In Afghanistan"</a>. rferl.org<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.rferl.org/Content/Archeologists_Find_Giant_Sleeping_Buddha_In_Afghanistan_/1197572.html" class="external free" title="http://www.rferl.org/Content/Archeologists_Find_Giant_Sleeping_Buddha_In_Afghanistan_/1197572.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.rferl.org/Content/Archeologists_Find_Giant_Sleeping_Buddha_In_Afghanistan_/1197572.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 29 October 2008</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Archaeologists+Find+Giant+%27Sleeping%27+Buddha+In+Afghanistan&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=rferl.org&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.rferl.org%2FContent%2FArcheologists_Find_Giant_Sleeping_Buddha_In_Afghanistan_%2F1197572.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Buddhas_of_Bamyan"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
